  plantName: Grass
  description: Grass is a widespread, typically green, herbaceous plant from the
    Poaceae family, characterized by narrow leaves, jointed stems, and extensive
    root systems. Covering roughly half of the earth's terrestrial surface, it plays
    crucial roles in soil stabilization, animal foraging, and providing essential
    food sources like rice, wheat, and corn.
